A passenger ferry sank off the coast of Guatemala while being towed to port.
Fifty-nine  people drowned and 6 are missing.
The ferry ran out of fuel mid-way on a regular 16- mile run across Amatique Bay and sank while a tugboat was towing it to shore.
A  Spanish citizen was reported dead, but his wife and son survived.
The victim was  working with a Spanish technical aid and economic development mission in Guatemala.
The nationality of the other victims was not known.
Navy patrol boats, fishing vessels  and private citizens have been searching for survivors and recovering bodies. 
